Re: auto backing up of wallet.dat

Bitcointalk

2010-08-27 01:13:42 UTC - [11]Original Post

   If you read it into memory and write it out, it could fail in tight
   memory situations.
   Iʼm looking for something like copyfile(const char* from, const char*
   to) or copyfile(path from, path to), preferably something in Boost if
   it has it.  If you find it for me, itʼs more likely Iʼll get to
   implementing it.
   [12]Quote from: nelisky on August 26, 2010, 01:21:57 AM
   As for the file copy, why add to the boost dependency? I for one would
   love to get a core lib with very little deps.
   We require Boost for JSON and a dozen things replacing dependencies on
   wxWidgets.  Boost is good, portable stuff, we should not shy away from
   it.
